HEADWORD: Charpie
<hw>Char"pie</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., properly
fem. p. p. of OF. <ets>charpir</ets>, <ets>carpir</ets>, to pluck, fr.
L. <ets>carpere</ets>. Cf. <er>Carpet</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>Straight threads obtained by unraveling old linen cloth; -- used
for surgical dressings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

